5:
HELLO, PALPEBRA! The ladies here are
the best!
8:
You've said that about every place
we've been to.
11:
And I've meant it every time I said it.
Each town has its own trends and
fashions and its own kind of beauty.
They can't be comparedâ€”ergo,
they're all the best.
14:
Or at least, better than the back of
beyond where I used to live. There
weren't even people there!
19:
Hey. We're here to look for clues
about your sister. Or did you forget?
22:
What? Can't I let go of my troubles
for even a second? You want me to
just suffer?
27:
Well, if you're going to be an ass
about it...
32:
I didn't forget, Nimbus. We're here to
look into reports of rampaging
dragons over on that mountain.
37:
I don't think Enith will be there... But
it's something to go on.
41:
However, the master of the land has
closed the mountain to outsiders. He
would not even treat with Lilie.
45:
Then I guess it's time to bring on the
charm.
49:
Let me introduce you to my
girlfriend, Madam Fleur.
54:
The hell? Think all your blood's
rushing in the opposite direction
from your brain.
60:
Forgive him, Madam. My friends
aren't very good with words, but
they CAN fight.
62:
Don't worry. I promise we'll save your
family.
65:
Thank you, Remnith. You're the only
one I can depend on!
71:
Spill it, Remnith. How did that
woman get us onto this mountain?
76:
It's simple. She's married to the
landlord.
81: Is that why you approached her?
84:
Nah, it was a coincidence. What can
I say? All meetings are fate.
89: You're gonna get stabbed one day.
92:
No, we're not actually like that. We
just got to talkingâ€”that's all.
97:
All right, but why did they close off
the mountain in the first place?
106:
The dad's some kind of herbalist. He
wanted to pick and mix all the
medicine himself, so he
monopolized this whole area.
109: All this for a few plants?
112:
Oh, I'm sure he owns way more than
this mountain. But now, regret has
reared his ugly head.
114:
You see, by keeping people out, he's
turned this place into a paradise for
dragons. Ironic how, in his desperate
attempt to protect, he only made
things worse.
120:
Wait. So the only problem here is
that there are too MANY dragons?
124: Exactly. They're not rampaging at all.
126:
But still, I promised I would help...
Sorry for dragging you guys into this.
129: We don't mind. Let's find those herbs.
138: Hey, fellas. Mind letting us through?
148:
Haha... Guess they smelled dragon
blood on me...
153:
There. That should be enough to last
you a few years.
158:
Say, how would you all like to work
as hunters for our family?
163:
But I have a better idea. Why not
open the mountain to the public?
167:
The more people tramping around
this place, the fewer dragon's there'll
be.
169:
Plus, these herbs aren't exclusive to
this mountain. If more people knew
about them, they could gather them
from other places. There's more
than enough to go around.
176:
It's your job to fight disease! We
can't just hoard everything for
ourselves. For my sake, please stop
running from the truth!
185:
For that family, at least... But what
about you, Remnith? That guy was
practically begging you to marry his
daughter.
190:
Yeah, I might regret not taking him
up on his offer. That girl was really
something...
193:
Wonder where her strength came
from...
196:
I think it's because she wanted to
make things right.
199:
She said it was her dream to go into
medicine and help people, like her
dad. But then she got sick, and her
dad turned paranoid, so she
blamed herself for everything...
202: I mean, I'm only guessing, but...
204:
She wanted to make things right,
huh?
208: ...Was it the same with you, Enith?
